  "text": "Here we consider the model introduced by Gai and Kapadia in [CITATION_1] . They consider a simple (yet rich) model of interlinked balance-sheets and study it with tools borrowed from the theory of complex networks [CITATION_2] . In the present paper we extend the analysis made in [CITATION_3] to account for properties empirically observed in real financial networks, notably heterogeneous degree distributions, heterogeneous assets distributions and degree correlations among connected banks. Our major findings are:",
